This paper focuses on developing a tool for suggesting code snippets given natural language queries related to APIs. This involves translating user queries into APIs of interest and synthesizing idiomatic code based on patterns learned from open-source code repositories. The paper also introduces structured call sequences as a generalized form of method call sequences. Overall, the paper's focus on tool development and natural language processing suggests that it is most likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. However, the paper also touches on programming languages (cs.PL), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG), making these sub-categories also likely.
